      "ESSeqNum": 9,
      "FacilityID": 24813,
      "SummaryText": "EPC.  Copies have been supplied to the Maine Emergency Management Agency, the town of Searsport and the neighboring town of Stockton Springs.\n\n\n7.0    PLANS FOR IMPROVEMENT\n\nGAC Chemical has had a solid safety record for many years.  Management continues to place the highest priority on the safety and environmental programs for the facility.  Improvements in the programs occur through ongoing review and annual updates by employees in all areas of production, maintenance, supervision and management.\n\nThe facility has a HAZMAT team on site and has an informal arrangement with third party HAZMAT responders for services on an as-needed basis.  A formal relationship is currently in final negotiations with a contract being reviewed by GAC Chemical Corporation for a HAZMAT services provider to provide response and other related services."
